Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, trim and peel half the @carrot{1/2}(trimmed and peeled) (double for 4p).

Run the #peeler{} down the length of the carrot to create long ribbons, stopping at the core.

Zest and juice half the @lime{1/2}(zested and juiced) (double for 4p).

Pop the lime juice into a large #bowl{} and mix with three-quarters of the @mayo{2%sachets}.

Add the carrot ribbons to the bowl. Season with salt and pepper, mix together, then set aside.

Lay the @Irish chicken breast{320%g} out on a #board{}.

Place your hand flat on top of the chicken breast.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

Repeat with the other breast(s).

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh. It will still taste delicious once cooked!

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the chicken steaks and season with salt and pepper.

Cook through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, reduce the heat to low and add the lime zest, @teriyaki sauce{1%sachet} and @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice) to the pan, stirring to combine.

Remove from the heat and turn the chicken in the sauce to evenly coat.

When the wedges are almost done, separate the @brioche buns{2}.

Pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

When everything is ready, spread a little of the remaining mayo over each bun base.

Divide the carrot ribbons between buns.

Top with the teriyaki chicken steaks and close with the bun lids.

Serve your teriyaki burgers with the sesame potato wedges alongside.